.TH "WebGLRenderingContext.stencilOpSeparate" "JS" "March 12, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebGLRenderingContext.stencilOpSeparate \- WebGLRenderingContext:
stencilOpSeparate() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGLRenderingContext.stencilOpSeparate()\f[B]\f[R]
method of the WebGL API sets the front and/or back\-facing stencil test
actions.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
stencilOpSeparate(face, fail, zfail, zpass)
.EE
.SS Parameters
The \f[CR]fail\f[R], \f[CR]zfail\f[R] and \f[CR]zpass\f[R] parameters
accept all constants listed below.
.TP
\f[B]face\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying whether the front and/or back stencil
state is updated.
The possible values are:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.FRONT\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.BACK\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]gl.FRONT_AND_BACK\f[R]
.RE
.TP
\f[B]fail\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the function to use when the stencil test
fails.
The default value is \f[CR]gl.KEEP\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]zfail\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the function to use when the stencil test
passes, but the depth test fails.
The default value is \f[CR]gl.KEEP\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]zpass\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the function to use when both the stencil
test and the depth test pass, or when the stencil test passes and there
is no depth buffer or depth testing is disabled.
The default value is \f[CR]gl.KEEP\f[R].
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH CONSTANTS
.TP
\f[B]gl.KEEP\f[R]
Keeps the current value.
.TP
\f[B]gl.ZERO\f[R]
Sets the stencil buffer value to 0.
.TP
\f[B]gl.REPLACE\f[R]
Sets the stencil buffer value to the reference value as specified by
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.stencilFunc()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]gl.INCR\f[R]
Increments the current stencil buffer value.
Clamps to the maximum representable unsigned value.
.TP
\f[B]gl.INCR_WRAP\f[R]
Increments the current stencil buffer value.
Wraps stencil buffer value to zero when incrementing the maximum
representable unsigned value.
.TP
\f[B]gl.DECR\f[R]
Decrements the current stencil buffer value.
Clamps to 0.
.TP
\f[B]gl.DECR_WRAP\f[R]
Decrements the current stencil buffer value.
Wraps stencil buffer value to the maximum representable unsigned value
when decrementing a stencil buffer value of 0.
.TP
\f[B]gl.INVERT\f[R]
Inverts the current stencil buffer value bitwise.
.SH EXAMPLES
The stencil testing is disabled by default.
To enable or disable stencil testing, use the \f[CR]enable()\f[R] and
\f[CR]disable()\f[R] methods with the argument
\f[CR]gl.STENCIL_TEST\f[R].
.IP
.EX
gl.enable(gl.STENCIL_TEST);
gl.stencilOpSeparate(gl.FRONT, gl.INCR, gl.DECR, gl.INVERT);
.EE
.PP
To get the current information about stencil and depth pass or fail,
query the following constants with \f[CR]getParameter()\f[R].
.IP
.EX
gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_FAIL);
gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_PASS_DEPTH_PASS);
gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_PASS_DEPTH_FAIL);
gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_BACK_FAIL);
gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_BACK_PASS_DEPTH_PASS);
gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_BACK_PASS_DEPTH_FAIL);
gl.getParameter(gl.STENCIL_BITS);
.EE
